      },
      "date": "2013-01-07 07:33:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nIt looks like the patch got changed back to a single ROOT FID, but the commit comment is still describing the original range of reserved sequences. Also, the reserved sequence range is still declared in lustre_idl.h, but doesn't appear to be used. \n\nI'm not agains this change otherwise, but you need to get agreement with Mike and Fan Yong, because you are all changing the same parts of the code.",
