    {
      "id": "e1d65eeb327dd346ebfb2116993969982620944e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-08 06:03:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nI do not oppose to assign special FID for \"ROOT\", as long as it can properly handle the old client which has already hold IGIF formatted \"ROOT\" FID.\n\nIn my LFSCK 1.5 patches (http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4904), the new \"ROOT\" with non-IGIF FID will be exposed directly to client, and related OI mappings will be inserted into the OI file. For the existing \"ROOT\" upgraded from old 1.8 or 2.x device, IGIF formatted FID is still valid.\n\nSo just depends on your patches or mine to be approved and landed firstly. I do not mind to rebase my patches if yours or Tappro first.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
